    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey so i've been watching the pigeons and sparrows in the park near my apartment lately and something weird is happening. they aren't just flying around randomly anymore. like, i noticed yesterday that a huge group of them all landed on the north side of the fountain at the exact same time right before that crazy storm hit. then this morning they were all making these specific little chirping sounds in a rhythm right before the fog rolled in. it's like... they're actually signaling the changes in the air. have you ever heard of birds doing this kind of coordinated signaling for weather? it feels too consistent to be a coincidence.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
