      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "It sounds like you've made some very keen observations about the local bird behavior! While we can't confirm they are consciously signaling weather, many bird species do exhibit complex, coordinated behaviors in response to environmental changes. These subtle shifts in flock patterns or vocalizations are often indicators that they are reacting to changes in barometric pressure, wind shifts, or atmospheric humidity before we notice them. Your consistent sightings suggest these birds might be highly sensitive to the local weather patterns.",
